08/07/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- EU Commission Vice President and Transport and Energy Commissioner Loyola de Palacio arrived in Bulgaria Thursday (8 July) at the invitation of Energy Minister Milko Kovachev.
De Palacio's first stop was the site of the proposed Belene nuclear power plant.
She is expected to convey EC support for the project during an upcoming meeting with Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg.
In other news, President Georgi Parvanov is in Moscow, marking the 125th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between Bulgaria and Russia.
On Wednesday, he and counterpart Vladimir Putin discussed possible Russian investments in Bulgaria.
Russian firms expect to participate in the tender for construction of the Belene plant.
(News.bg, Mediapool.bg, Sega - 08/07/04)
